2026-03-05 | Longest Substring with Exactly K Distinct Characters

	Question
Given string s and integer k, return the length of the longest substring containing exactly k distinct characters.

	Approach
1.	Use sliding window technique with two pointers:
		left and right.
2.	Maintain a hashmap storing frequency of characters in the current window.
3.	Expand the window by moving right pointer and updating frequency.
4.	If distinct characters become greater than k:
		shrink window from the left until distinct ≤ k.
5.	Whenever distinct == k:
		update the maximum length.
6.	Continue until the string ends.
7.	If no valid substring is found, return -1.

	Time Complexity
1.	O(n)

	Space Complexity
1.	O(26) → constant for lowercase letters

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    int longestKSubstr(string s, int k) {
        unordered_map<char,int> freq;
        int left = 0;
        int ans = -1;

        for (int right = 0; right < s.size(); right++) {
            freq[s[right]]++;

            while (freq.size() > k) {
                freq[s[left]]--;
                if (freq[s[left]] == 0)
                    freq.erase(s[left]);
                left++;
            }

            if (freq.size() == k)
                ans = max(ans, right - left + 1);
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
